```

**Commands:**
- `pnpm test` ‚Äî run tests in watch mode
- `pnpm test:ci` ‚Äî run tests once (CI)
- `pnpm check:all` ‚Äî type-check + lint + test:ci (run before every commit)
- `pnpm test:e2e` ‚Äî Playwright E2E tests (requires dev server)

**Test conventions:**
- Unit tests live next to the code or in `src/test/unit/`
- Use factories from `src/test/helpers.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode test data
- Mock external services (Clerk, Neon, Upstash) ‚Äî test business logic, not integrations
- Name test files `*.test.ts` or `*.test.tsx`

## Auth Architecture

Dual-mode authentication ‚Äî Clerk for web, JWT for mobile:

```
Request arrives
  ‚îú‚îÄ Has Clerk session cookie?
  ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ Yes ‚Üí resolve via Clerk ‚Üí get internal user by clerkId
  ‚îú‚îÄ Has Authorization: Bearer header?
  ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ Yes ‚Üí verify JWT (jose) ‚Üí get internal user by userId
  ‚îî‚îÄ Neither?
      ‚îî‚îÄ Return 401 via ApiError.unauthorised()
```

**Key files:**
- `src/lib/auth/get-auth.ts` ‚Äî dual-mode resolver, single entry point
- `src/lib/auth/resolve-clerk-user.ts` ‚Äî Clerk webhook ‚Üí local user upsert
- `src/lib/mobile-jwt.ts` ‚Äî `signMobileJwt()` / `verifyMobileJwt()`
- `src/lib/auth-routing.ts` ‚Äî public routes, auth routes, role-based access
- `src/middleware.ts` ‚Äî Clerk middleware, protects non-public routes

**Roles:** `admin`, `user` (defined in `src/types/index.ts`, stored on user record)

**Webhook sync:** Clerk fires `user.created` / `user.updated` / `user.deleted` ‚Üí `POST /api/webhooks/clerk` ‚Üí `resolveClerkUser()` upserts local record.

## Key Patterns

### API Route Handler

```typescript
// src/app/api/example/route.ts
import { getAuth } from '@/lib/auth/get-auth';
import { ok, created, handleError, ApiError } from '@/lib/api-response';
import { checkRateLimit, publicRateLimiter } from '@/lib/rate-limit';
import { getRequestContext } from '@/lib/request-context';
import { parsePagination } from '@/lib/validations';

export async function GET(request: NextRequest) {
  try {
    const { ip } = await getRequestContext();
    const { success } = await checkRateLimit(ip, publicRateLimiter);
    if (!success) throw ApiError.rateLimited();

    const { page, pageSize } = parsePagination(request.nextUrl.searchParams);
    // ... query database ...
    return ok({ data: items, pagination: { page, pageSize, total, totalPages } });
  } catch (error) {
    return handleError(error);
  }
}
```

